      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sound 2008 Porsche Cayman S, powered by the 3.4L M97 flat-six engine featuring VarioCam Plus for an optimized torque curve across the rev range. This mid-engine platform offers a superior polar moment of inertia, paired with a tactile 6-speed manual transaxle that ensures precise gear synchronization. The chassis retains its factory rigidity, supported by a MacPherson strut suspension geometry that delivers exceptional lateral grip and communicative steering feedback. This example is equipped with four-piston Brembo monobloc calipers and cross-drilled rotors, providing consistent thermal management under load. While the exterior exhibits minor road-going patina consistent with its 'good' status, the powertrain remains robust with no signs of bore scoring or IMS bearing issues. This is a driver-focused specimen with a linear power delivery and an evocative exhaust note.",
